'AUX COPY' COPIES MEMORY BETWEENMAIN AND AUXILIARY MEMORY. 'BRUN' ITTO INSTALL. THEN YOU WILL BE ABLE TOUSE '&' COMMANDS TO COPY MEMORY; ASFOLLOWS: & start; end; destination; modestart - STARTING ADDRESS OF THEBLOCK OF MEMORY TO COPYend - ENDING ADDRESS OF THE BLOCK OFMEMORY TO COPYdestination - STARTING ADDRESS OFTHE PLACE TO COPY TOmode - 0 TO COPY FROM MAIN TOAUXILIARY; 1 TO COPY FROM AUXILIARYTO MAIN